  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As per the p2p spec (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/phase0/p2p-interface.md#topics-and-messages):\r\n\r\n```Each gossipsub message has a maximum size of GOSSIP_MAX_SIZE. Clients MUST reject (fail validation) messages that are over this size limit. Likewise, clients MUST NOT emit or propagate messages larger than this limit.```\r\n\r\nAs far as I can tell, we are only checking for GOSSIP_MAX_SIZE on incoming messages, but we don't do it for outgoing messages.  We should be doing both.",
